	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />There are three regions, as I understand it:
<br /><ul><li>Super Famicom (Japan, Hong Kong): Japanese cart shape, NTSC CIC, NTSC PPU </li><li>Super NES (North America): North American cart shape, NTSC CIC, NTSC PPU </li><li>Super NES (PAL version): Japanese cart shape, PAL CIC, PAL PPU </li></ul>
<br />RetroZone cart shells are Japanese shape but have the alignment cutouts to also fit in North American systems.
<br />
<br />Games with the protection may be doing various PPU checks, possibly including a check for 50 Hz or 60 Hz (like <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/Detect_TV_system" class="postlink">this on NES</a>).

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


